<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1035,1350]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1035,1062]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. A Taiwanese species with pinkish red pronotum having central apex dark brown and margins yellowish brown; elytra dark brown, margins yellowish brown (Jeng did not specify extent or width of the margins); posterior margin of 
<date box="[267,301,1108,1134]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">V7</date>
rounded; posterior margin of aedeagal sheath sternite two lobed; ML wide at base, narrowing gradually just posterior to the origins of the lobes on the LL; narrow apical portion is Â¼ as wide as basal portion; anteromedian margin of sheath tergite broadly and narrowly produced and truncate. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jeng" box="[1017,1280,1179,1206]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Jeng" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" pagination="247 - 262" refId="ref118190" refString="Jeng, M. L., Yang, P. S. &amp; Lai, J. (2003 b) Notes on the genus Luciola (Coleoptera, Lampyridae, Luciolinae) of Taiwan. Special Bulletin of the Japanese Society of Coleopterolog y, 6, 247 - 262." type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="b">
Jeng 
<emphasis box="[1074,1123,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">et al</emphasis>
. (2003b: 251)
</bibRefCitation>
distinguished this species from 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1933" box="[347,534,1216,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roseicollis">
<emphasis box="[347,492,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">L. roseicollis</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
by its much smaller size, and from the similarly coloured 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura" authorityName="Matsumura Smaller" authorityYear="1928" box="[1183,1437,1216,1242]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kagiana">
<emphasis box="[1183,1302,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">L. kagiana</emphasis>
Matsumura
</taxonomicName>
by the much larger size of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura Smaller" authorityYear="1928" box="[457,547,1252,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kagiana">
<emphasis box="[457,547,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">kagiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Inconsistencies with the identifications of various of these similarly coloured 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paruula Kiesenwetter. Matsumura" authorityYear="1928" box="[151,237,1288,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,237,1288,1314]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Luciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are discussed under the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1928" box="[670,825,1288,1314]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curtithorax">
<emphasis box="[670,825,1288,1314]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">L. curtithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
above, and requires further investigation. 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" firstAuthor="Chen" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" refId="ref115752" refString="Chen, T. R. (2003) The fireflies of Taiwan. Field Image Publisher, Taipei, 256 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2003">Chen (2003: 169)</bibRefCitation>
figures a â 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Paruula Kiesenwetter. Matsumura" authorityYear="1928" box="[323,409,1324,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[323,409,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Luciola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 3â which is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jeng et Yang" authorityYear="2003" box="[584,667,1324,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Luciola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satoi">
<emphasis box="[584,667,1324,1349]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">L. satoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Jeng pers. comm.).
</paragraph>
